      "type": "short",
      "question": "Find the inverse of matrix A = [[3, 1], [2, 1]] using the adjugate method.",
      "keyPoints": [
        "Find determinant: det(A) = 3\u00d71 - 1\u00d72 = 1",
        "Find cofactor matrix: [[1, -2], [-1, 3]]",
        "Find adjugate by transposing: [[1, -1], [-2, 3]]",
        "A\u207b\u00b9 = (1/det) \u00d7 adj(A) = [[1, -1], [-2, 3]]"
      ],
      "marks": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "q-2",
      "type": "short",
      "question": "State and prove the condition for a square matrix to be invertible.",
      "keyPoints": [
        "Condition: Matrix is invertible iff det(A) \u2260 0 (or rank = n)",
        "If invertible: AA\u207b\u00b9 = I, take det: det(A)\u00d7det(A\u207b\u00b9) = 1, so det(A) \u2260 0",
        "Conversely, if det(A) \u2260 0: A\u207b\u00b9 = adj(A)/det(A) exists",
        "Thus: invertible \u21d4 det(A) \u2260 0 \u21d4 full rank"
      ],
      "marks": 5
    },
